      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TARA VICTORY NZ (1) was far from disgraced when fourth behind some smart mares in a higher-graded race at Menangle last start. Led from wider when missing by a head here two back and won two in a row prior. Can take advantage of the inside draw. NEATNTIDY (10) is close to a win after placing in his last three starts, two of them from this row. Missed by a nose at this circuit and distance last time. With even luck he could break through. CONISTON (9) hasn't raced since October's SA Derby but has strong records both when fresh and at the distance and has been readied with a solid trial. ROYAL APPOINTMENT (8) missed by just a head as runner-up at this circuit and distance last time and draws for a nice trail.",
